message.content: cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CYBER, cs.SY - This paper discusses the ethical implications of artificial reinforcement learning agents, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence and robotics. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the general method of training agents, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper touches on the potential risks and harm that can be inflicted on these agents, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
